import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Ensure Date is in datetime format
data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%m/%d/%Y')

# Set the date as the index for easier plotting
data.set_index('Date', inplace=True)

# Define the variables to plot
variables = ['M1 Money Supply', 'Real Exchange Rate', 'S&P 500 Index (Adj Close)', 'Inflation Rate (CPI)']

# Plot line charts for each variable
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))
for i, var in enumerate(variables, 1):
    plt.subplot(2, 2, i)
    plt.plot(data.index, data[var], label=var)
    plt.title(f'Trend of {var} Over Time')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel(var)
    plt.legend()
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('line_charts_trend_over_time.png', dpi=300)
plt.show()

# Plot histograms for each variable
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))
for i, var in enumerate(variables, 1):
    plt.subplot(2, 2, i)
    sns.histplot(data[var], bins=30, kde=True)
    plt.title(f'Distribution of {var}')
    plt.xlabel(var)
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('trends_over_time.png', dpi=300)
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
# Convert 'Date' column to datetime format
data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%m/%d/%Y')

# Extract the exchange rate for the reference date (July 24, 2021)
reference_date = pd.Timestamp('2021-07-24')
reference_exchange_rate = data.loc[data['Date'] == reference_date, 'Real Exchange Rate']

# Extract the most recent exchange rate
current_exchange_rate = data.loc[data['Date'] == data['Date'].max(), 'Real Exchange Rate']

# Calculate currency devaluation
if not reference_exchange_rate.empty and not current_exchange_rate.empty:
    reference_exchange_rate = reference_exchange_rate.values[0]
    current_exchange_rate = current_exchange_rate.values[0]
    currency_devaluation = ((current_exchange_rate - reference_exchange_rate) / reference_exchange_rate) * 100
    currency_devaluation
else:
    currency_devaluation = None

currency_devaluation

# Find the closest date to the reference date
closest_reference_date = data.iloc[(data['Date'] - reference_date).abs().argsort()[:1]]['Date'].values[0]

# Extract the exchange rate for the closest reference date
reference_exchange_rate = data.loc[data['Date'] == closest_reference_date, 'Real Exchange Rate'].values[0]

# Recalculate currency devaluation
currency_devaluation = ((current_exchange_rate.values[0] - reference_exchange_rate) / reference_exchange_rate) * 100
